ould also instant retiere, but i try to roleplay my cleric or wizzi or pally as good as i can.<br><br>Sage Seelendieb Soultaker<br>Warlock<br><br>P.S. This shouldnt be a rant ... more than the facts as i see them <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uleldariluthiniel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Leldari Luthiniel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 190<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/5/02 3:10:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3324.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Just Venting </span><hr size=1> I too have been known to look for the highest cleric but I take what is available and I am grateful. That is my point...it isn't the search for the highest res. It is being angry at someone who just did you a favor you requested. She had not even asked the other paladin if he would res her. She was angry at the fact that by doing as she had requested (which she could have simply clicked no to) she was unable to get the higher res that MIGHT be available to her. Had I seen the higher paladin I would have even suggested she ask for the higher res. All I am asking for is simple courtesy. After all what does a thank you cost....nothing.<br><br>PS and Kerroll you are absolutely right Hell has frozen over and Norrath as we knew it ended...paladins are actually occasionally useful. <br><br>PPS I miss the David Hasselhoff pics...he may not be much in brains who knows but he made good eye candy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uigota.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Igota</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 610<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/5/02 3:33:31 pm)</font><br> 